notesStmt.note: Title from title page (f. i recto).
Title of second part (f. 136r): Versos de Bartolomé Leonardo de Argensola, capellan de la Emperatriz doña Maria de Austria y rector de Villa Hermosa
Spine title: Poesias de los Argensolas. Manuscrito del siglo XVI.

msContents.summary: Collection of poems by Lupercio Leonardo de Argensola (f. 1r-122v), with a brief addition containing some works by Bartolomé Leonardo de Argenso (f. 123r-129v). Also includes a second section consisting of poems by Bartolomé Leonardo de Argensola (f. 136r-306r).

supportDesc.extent: 313 leaves : 194 x 142 (149 x 95) mm. bound to 203 x 143 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, ii (modern paper) + 313 + ii (modern paper); [i], 1-124, [xii], 1-18, 20-126, 128-168, [iii], contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto; [i, 1-308], modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto. References in this record are to the modern foliation.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand, with additions and corrections in several other hands.

binding.p: 19th-century[?] half leather. Upper cover and spine detached.

origin.p: Written in Spain in the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Formerly in the collection of the Biblioteca de Salvá (gold crest on upper and lower cover); formerly owned by R. Foulché-Delbosc (Zacour-Hirsch).
